This paper is primarily focused on planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implementation of Picat's planner using tabling, which is a technique used in logic programming (cs.PL). The paper also discusses modeling techniques, which can be considered a topic in logic (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of structured data and term sharing, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS).
